summary: This is an email exchange between FBI personnel regarding the use of a Lyft account to provide transportation for a witness being interviewed for the Ghislaine Maxwell trial. The email includes a TextNow phone number and details about the planned rides.

persons.name: Paul Byrne
persons.context: FBI agent coordinating the use of a Lyft account to transport a witness for an interview related to the Maxwell trial.

connections.description: FBI colleagues coordinating logistics for witness transportation related to the Maxwell trial investigation.

events.title: Witness Interview Transportation Arranged
events.description: FBI agents arrange Lyft rides to transport a witness for an interview related to the Ghislaine Maxwell trial.

keyFacts: The FBI was using a Lyft account to transport a witness for an interview related to the Ghislaine Maxwell trial in July 2021.
The witness interview was associated with FBI case number 3027571.
A TextNow phone number was provided for coordination purposes as of July 6, 2021.
Two round-trip Lyft rides were planned for approximately 11 AM and 2 PM, each costing about $25.
